summary:
tl;dr Turn the SettingWithCopyWarning into an explicit error that you are forced to fix by setting
import pandas as pd pd.set_option(&#34;mode.chained_assignment&#34;, &#34;raise&#34;) Problem pandas is complaining to you with the following warning (which only shows up on first execution):
SettingWithCopyWarning: A value is trying to be set on a copy of a slice from a DataFrame. Solution Use pd.set_option(&quot;mode.chained_assignment&quot;, &quot;raise&quot;) to force yourself to actually fix the underlying piece of offending code.
